            Subject to these Terms, we grant you a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to use Dev Cockpit on any Mac devices you own or control, as permitted by your license agreement.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">5. User Responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">You agree to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-300 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>Use the App only for lawful purposes</li>
            <li>Not reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the App</li>
            <li>Not use the App to harm, threaten, or harass others</li>
            <li>Not use the App for unauthorized network scanning or security testing</li>
            <li>Comply with all applicable laws and regulations</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-300">
            Dev Cockpit and all associated content, features, and functionality are owned by Dev Cockpit and are protected by international copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
